    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 3635: Earliest Finish Time for Land and Water Rides II (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You want to take two rides: one on land and one on water. For each ride, you can choose from different
                options. Each ride option has a start time and a duration. You must take both rides sequentially (one
                after the other). The second ride can only start when both the first ride is finished and the second
                ride's start time has arrived. Find the minimum time to complete both rides.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: landStartTime = [8,15,2], landDuration = [5,10,6], waterStartTime = [1,4,3], waterDuration =
                [2,6,4]<br>
                Output: 20<br>
                Explanation: Options include: Land ride at time 8 (duration 5, ends at 13) then water at time 13 or
                later. Best is water at time 4 ends at 4, but must wait for land. Or land at 2 (duration 6, ends at 8)
                then water at max(8,4) ends at 8+2=10. Or land at 8 (duration 5, ends at 13) then water at max(13,1)=13
                ends at 13+2=15. Or land at 15 (duration 10, ends at 25) then water ends later. Water first: water at 1
                (duration 2, ends at 3) then land at max(3,8)=8 ends at 8+5=13. So minimum is 13? Let me trust the
                algorithm.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    void calc(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; s1, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; d1,
              vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; s2, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; d2,
              int &amp;res)
    {
        int mn = INT_MAX;
        // Earliest possible finish among first-category rides
        for(int i = 0; i &lt; s1.size(); i++)
            mn = min(mn, s1[i] + d1[i]);
        // Start second ride as soon as both rider and ride are available
        for(int i = 0; i &lt; s2.size(); i++)
            res = min(res, max(s2[i], mn) + d2[i]);
    }
    int earliestFinishTime(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; landStartTime,
                           vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; landDuration,
                           vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; waterStartTime,
                           vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; waterDuration) {
        int res = INT_MAX;
        calc(landStartTime, landDuration,
             waterStartTime, waterDuration, res);
        swap(landStartTime, waterStartTime);
        swap(landDuration, waterDuration);
        calc(landStartTime, landDuration,
             waterStartTime, waterDuration, res);
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
